@startuml f9-usage-metrics
title Flow 9 — Usage / token metrics queries

!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #5B6770
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "User" as u
participant "Frontend\n(chat /context ;\nUsage page)" as fe
participant "backend-facade" as facade
participant "RuntimeApiRoutes\n(runtime_api/http/routes.py)" as r
participant "ConversationContextBuilder\n(agent_runtime/api/usage_service.py)" as ccb
participant "UsageQueryService\n(agent_runtime/api/usage_service.py)" as uqs
participant "PersistencePort\n(RuntimeModelCallUsageRecord,\nRuntimeRunUsageRecord,\nCompressionEventRecord,\nModelPricingRecord)" as p
participant "UsageRollupLoop\n(runtime_worker/usage_rollup_loop.py)" as roll

note over u, roll
  Two distinct query surfaces:
   • /context — server-computed token headroom for the active conversation.
   • /v1/usage/* — rolled-up token + cost rows for the Usage page.
  All numbers come from telemetry rows written by the worker during runs.
  Nothing is recomputed from raw events.
  Pricing changes do NOT retroactively rewrite history.
end note

== Surface 1 — In-chat /context ==

u -> fe : type "/context" in the active conversation
fe -> facade : GET /v1/agent/conversations/{id}/context
facade -> r : forwarded
r -> ccb : ConversationContextBuilder.build(\n   org_id, user_id, conversation_id)

ccb -> p : fetch latest run's RuntimeModelCallUsageRecord rows,\nCompressionEventRecord rows,\nactive ModelPricingRecord
p --> ccb : telemetry tuple

ccb -> ccb : sum input + output tokens across all model calls,\nfold compression events,\ncompute headroom_pct = (max_input - used) / max_input * 100\ncollapse subagent rows to supervisor for breakdown
ccb --> r : ConversationContextResponse {\n  context_window,\n  used_tokens,\n  available_tokens,\n  headroom_pct,\n  compression_events[],\n  per_subagent_breakdown[]\n}
r --> facade : 200 + JSON
facade --> fe : same
fe -->> u : headroom pill: "12 345 / 200 000 (94% free)"

note right of ccb
  ConversationContextBuilder is stateless and pure.
  It never calls the LLM. Subagent rows are collapsed
  to the supervisor before per-task breakdowns are reported.
end note

== Surface 2 — Usage page (per-user) ==

u -> fe : open Usage page (week selector)
fe -> facade : GET /v1/usage/me?period=2026-W18
facade -> uqs : list_user_usage(org_id, user_id, period)
uqs -> uqs : parse_period → days_between
uqs -> p : SELECT RuntimeRunUsageRecord\n  WHERE org_id, user_id, date IN window
p --> uqs : rows
uqs -> uqs : _RollupBucket per day → rollup_user_rows
uqs --> facade : UsageResponse {days[], totals}
facade --> fe : per-day series + grand totals

opt Per-connector breakdown
  fe -> facade : GET /v1/usage/me/connectors?period=...
  facade -> uqs : list_user_connector_usage(...)
  uqs -> p : SELECT RuntimeModelCallUsageRecord\n  WHERE connector attribution
  uqs --> facade : ConnectorUsageRow[]\n(one bucket per connector,\nincludes "no_connector" bucket)
  facade --> fe : connector breakdown
end

opt Org-wide (admin only; RBAC checked)
  fe -> facade : GET /v1/usage/org?period=...
  facade -> uqs : list_org_usage(org_id, period, caller_role=admin)
  uqs -> p : rollup_org_rows
  uqs --> facade : OrgUsageRow[]
  facade --> fe : org-level chart
end

== Where the rows come from ==

note over roll, p
  RuntimeModelCallUsageRecord rows are written by
  AssistantRunMetrics + PostgresUsageRecorder at
  run completion for each MODEL_CALL_COMPLETED chunk
  (fields: input_tokens, output_tokens, cached_input_tokens,
  reasoning_tokens, connector_slug, purpose).

  UsageRollupLoop runs on RUNTIME_USAGE_ROLLUP_INTERVAL_SECONDS
  interval: aggregates per-call rows → daily RuntimeRunUsageRecord.
  CostCalculator converts tokens to micro-USD using the
  ModelPricingRecord active at write time. Pricing changes
  do NOT retroactively alter existing history rows.
end note

roll -> p : rollup recent un-aggregated model_call rows\n(idempotent: already-aggregated rows skipped)

@enduml
